"'''Garageland'''" is a song by English [[punk rock]] band [[The Clash]] featured as the final track for their 1977 debut album ''[[The Clash (album)|The Clash]]''.

The song was penned by [[Joe Strummer]] as a response to music journalist [[Charles Shaar Murray]], who, after a gig in 1976, wrote a review saying that they were "the kind of garage band who should be returned to the garage immediately", and also to both the fans and the record company, with which they had signed a contract for Â£100,000 on 25 January 1977,{{Sfn|Gray|2005|p=216}} that they would still remain the same as they were before the signing.{{Sfn|Coon|1977}}

